<h1>Roberto Zoia</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://zoia.org/now">zoia.org/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Lima

Peru
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I’m a Project Manager for a leading company in the metal mechanics industry in Peru.  I’m also building side businesses.  I write at zoia.org.  Compulsive reader.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I try to do meaningful work and my best every time. I believe in sharing what I learn and know with others.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Life is not only about fulfilling one owns needs according to Maslow’s hierarchy… We achieve our greatest potential when we try to do our best while helping others do the same. 
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
About business ideas:  validate your idea first!  Don’t fall in the “solution looking for a problem” syndrome.  
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“The One Thing” by Gary Keller.  
</p>

